National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Factual Report
Location: Nulato, AK
Accident Number: GAA18CA320
Date & Time: 06/01/2018, 2330 AKD
Registration: N3937M
Aircraft: PIPER PA 12
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event: Hard landing
Injuries: 2 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation - Personal
The pilot reported that, while landing off airport on an upslope of a ridge, the tailwheel-
equipped airplane "touched down harder than preferred". He applied full throttle, initiated a 
go-around, and attempted to turn towards the downslope side of the hill. The airplane briefly 
became airborne but then aerodynamically stalled and nosed down into the tundra. 
The airplane sustained substantial damage to the engine mount. 
The pilot reported that there were no preaccident mechanical failures or malfunctions with the 
airplane that would have precluded normal operation.
